{
  "texts": [
    "For example, we were able to reconstruct how government-led imaginaries have been adopted by corporate stakeholders in Germany and China.",
    "This allows us to better understand how AI as an object of (science) communication is actively negotiated between powerful stakeholders and how this process and the power relations vary across different countries and their different sociopolitical structures.",
    "As the empirical work faced limitations due to limited access to different Chinese stakeholders, this yields constraints when comparing the countries.",
    "While we have sought to reflect these differences in the analyses, future research needs to continue unpacking how powerful stakeholders mobilise AI and the high level of imagination around this technology for their own interest.",
    "In this negotiation of different future visions of AI and society, stakeholders in different countries have differing amounts of power and resources."
  ]
}